name: Graceful Symmetry
description:
Gardenia is a genus of 142 species[2] of flowering plants in the coffee family. The flowers are solitary or in small clusters, white, or pale yellow. Flowering is from about mid-spring to mid-summer and many species are strongly scented.

This beautiful painting measures 12 x 12 inches and is painted on 300 lb. Saunders-Waterford cold press paper.

name: Northern Cardinal
description:
The Northern Cardinal (Cardinalis cardinalis) is a North American bird in the genus Cardinalis; it is also known colloquially as the redbird or common cardinal. 

This beautiful painting measures 8.750 x 10.500 inches and is painted on 300 lb. Saunders-Waterford cold press paper.
